		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName><sic>Pittsburg</sic></placeName> <date>Nov. 18<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1852</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Rev. Mr Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir&#33;</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Pardon my encroachment on<lb/> your time when in a charitable occasion<lb/> I venture to impose a little on your good<lb/> nature.  A few days before <date>New Years</date> a man<lb/> by the name of <persName>Levy</persName> a brother to <persName>Mrs Tobias</persName><lb/> came to our city in a very lamentable sick<lb/> condition.  We have since taken every care<lb/> possible of him&#44; but in spite of the best<lb/> attention and medical advice he <sic>lay&#39;s</sic> on<lb/> the brink of death&#44; the doctors do not<lb/> suppose that he will be able to hold out<lb/> two days longer.  We have written several<lb/> letters to <persName>Mr Levy</persName> his brother in <placeName><sic>Chesnut</sic><lb/> Sts.</placeName> but to his shame&#44; he never answer<lb/> in to any of them.  We therefore beg your<lb/> kind mediation with <persName>Mrs Tobias</persName> or her<lb/> brother that they may take pity on their poor<lb/> dying brother&#44; he will hardly trouble them<lb/> much more in this world&#44; since I believe<lb/> that before this will reach you&#44; he may<lb/> be removed out of this vale of tears.  Let them<lb/> consider <del>reflect</del> their own mortality and reflect<lb/> on the sad fate of their unfortunate brother.</p>
			<pb n="1V"/>
				<p>His misfortune has caused us a great deal<lb/> of trouble and expense and his disease would<lb/> even <sic>dubble</sic> it.  Our family and <persName>Mr. Marcusson</persName><lb/> have been the only persons <sic>untill</sic> now who<lb/> visited him and endeavored to alleviate his<lb/> sufferings&#44; and his burial&#44; will of course<lb/> have to be done by us too.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I hope you will be kind enough to speak<lb/> to the above mentioned parties and soli&#45;<lb/>city their assistance&#44; and so oblige</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Yours Tr</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">very Respectfully</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><persName role="author">L Jarodawski</persName></p>
			<pb n="2V"/>
